fields.name: India
fields.description: Tourism in India is important for the country's economy and is growing rapidly. The World Travel and Tourism Council calculated that tourism generated ₹16.91 lakh crore (US$240 billion) or 9.2% of India's GDP in 2018 and supported 42.673 million jobs, 8.1% of its total employment.[1] The sector is predicted to grow at an annual rate of 6.9% to ₹32.05 lakh crore (US$450 billion) by 2028 (9.9% of GDP).[2] In October 2015, India's medical tourism sector was estimated to be worth US$3 billion, and it is projected to grow to US$7–8 billion by 2020.[3] In 2014, 184,298 foreign patients travelled to India to seek medical treatment.[4]

fields.name: USA
fields.description:
Tourism in the United States is a large industry that serves millions of international and domestic tourists yearly. Foreigners visit the U.S. to see natural wonders, cities, historic landmarks, and entertainment venues. Americans seek similar attractions, as well as recreation and vacation areas.

Tourism in the United States grew rapidly in the form of urban tourism during the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries. By the 1850s, tourism in the United States was well established both as a cultural activity and as an industry. New York City, Los Angeles, Chicago, Boston, Philadelphia, Washington, D.C.,

fields.name: Canada
fields.description: The second largest country in the world, Canada has no shortage of beautiful landscapes and unique sites for travelers to explore. From coast to coast to coast, the country is home to vibrant and culturally rich cities, along with incredible natural wonders.

fields.name: Thailand
fields.description: Thailand is a Southeast Asian country. It's known for tropical beaches, opulent royal palaces, ancient ruins and ornate temples displaying figures of Buddha. In Bangkok, the capital, an ultramodern cityscape rises next to quiet canalside communities and the iconic temples of Wat Arun, Wat Pho and the Emerald Buddha Temple (Wat Phra Kaew). Nearby beach resorts include bustling Pattaya and fashionable Hua Hin

fields.title: Jaipur, Rajasthan
fields.content:
Rajasthan is magnificent, Rajasthan is captivating, and its capital Jaipur provides a hot air ballooning experience over the picturesque Aravalis, magnificent forts. Around 50 (approx.) International travelers indulge in hot air balloon safari in Jaipur every day, which shows it is worth all the hype. You get to enjoy the 360-degree views of the capital of Rajasthan, which is the royal experience to cherish in the ‘Land of Maharajas.’ If you are on your honeymoon, then it would be very romantic to propose to your beloved one at an altitude of 1200 ft (approx.) amidst the golden hues of sunset. Return home with everlasting memories of Rajasthan, whether with family or your sweetheart.

 

Is Jaipur Worth The Hype: Yes! Catching a birds-eye view of the Pink City on a hot air balloon is one of the best things to do in Jaipur.

For How Long Ride will Last: 45 to 60 minutes (approx.)

Best Time for Activity: March to October

Average Height: 1200 ft – 5000 ft (approx.)
fields.author: Admin

fields.title: Goa
fields.content: Experiencing a magical hot air balloon ride over the sea in Goa is one of the best things to do in summer and winters. You will love enjoying the panoramic views of the Arabian Sea while perching yourself in a cozy hot air colorful balloon. You will get a chance to cruise in the sky with your friends or family or sweetheart in a spacious luxury basket. Before the activity, satiate your hunger with light onsite refreshments included in the hot air ballooning package. Get your camera ready for perfect sea cliff shots. Inside the hot air balloon basket, up to 10 people can accommodate in one single ride. Note that the cost of a private hot air balloon ride cost is whooping! Take your kids or parents on a hot air balloon ride in Goa beyond beaches.
fields.author: Admin

fields.title: White Water Rafting
fields.content: River rafting is among the best adventure sports in Uttarakhand. Perhaps it is one of the most sought-after adventure water sports done by almost every adventure freak during a trip to Uttarakhand. The gushing rapids of the river Ganges and Tons taking you in its own direction, throwing you up and down while you flip the paddles is one of the best experiences to embrace.
fields.author: Admin

fields.title: Trekking in The Himalayas
fields.content: The closeness of the mighty Himalayan ranges makes Uttarakhand one of the best places to indulge in extreme sports, and trekking is not the exception. The sky-kissing snow-capped peaks allow adventure enthusiasts to hit its best trekking trails, which is nothing less than a treat to the senses.
fields.author: Admin

fields.title: Tandem Paragliding in Mussoorie
fields.content: The best part of Tandem Paragliding in Mussoorie is that it does not require any prior experience or skill to enjoy it. Sit tight and simply hang on the ropes, and leave it on the pilot. Enjoy flying for around 15 to 20 minutes in the air and let the adrenaline take your nerves away. It is one of the best adventure sports to try in Uttarakhand.
fields.author: Admin

fields.title: Munnar In Monsoon
fields.content:
Nestled along the asymmetric slopes of the Nilgiri hills, this picturesque place is a must visit during the rainy season in Munnar. Situated at a distance of 3 km from Munnar this scenic place falls on the way to Top station and Mattupetti. Truly justifying its name, the lush green tea gardens and the scenic hills makes a great backdrop to capture.

Location: SH18, Kannan Devan Hills, Kerala 685612
Timings: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM
